34. Replace all occurrences of a specific word with another word in a string using regular expressions in
PHP.
<?php
// Original string
$text = "I love apples. Apples are my favorite fruit. I eat apples every day.";

// Replace 'apples' (case-insensitive) with 'mangoes'
$result = preg_replace("/apples/i", "mangoes", $text);

// Display the result
echo $result;
?>
